9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 553, L.D. 867, “An Act Regarding Pre-
10 need Funeral Insurance”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 24-A MRSA §2176, as amended by PL 1999, c. 258, §1, is further amended
14 to read:
15 §2176. Funeral and burial service contracts prohibited
16 An insurer may not contract or agree with any funeral director practitioner, funeral
17 establishment, mortuary establishment, cemetery, cemetery corporation or association,
18 crematorium, mausoleum or columbarium or any representative of any of these directors
19 practitioners or establishments to the effect that the director practitioner or establishment
20 shall must conduct the funeral, burial, or cremation or other disposal of the remains of any
21 individual insured by the insurer. An insurer may not retain, utilize or employ any director
22 or establishment as a producer or agency of the insurer and a director or establishment may
23 not act as or purport to be an insurance producer or engage in insurance producer activities.
24 Nothing in this section prevents This section does not prevent compliance with Title 39‑A,
25 section 216, or the use of an insurance policy, including, subject to the provisions of section
26 2420, the assignment of rights under life insurance contracts, to provide security for the
27 payment for a funeral, burial or cremation or, subject to chapter 27, the naming of a funeral
28 home establishment or funeral director practitioner as beneficiary under a life insurance
29 policy to provide payment for a funeral, burial or cremation. Nothing in this This section
30 prohibits does not prohibit the use of an insurance policy as an investment by a mortuary
31 trustee pursuant to Title 32, section 1401.
32 Sec. 2. 24-A MRSA §2176-A is enacted to read:
33 §2176-A. Disclosures required for sale of pre-need insurance in connection with
34 prearranged funerals
Page 1 - 132LR0695(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 553, L.D. 867
1 1. Definition. For purposes of this section, "pre-need insurance" means a type of life
2 insurance policy designed to cover the costs of funeral and burial services selected in a
3 statement of goods and services contract and for which the entire death benefit is paid
4 directly to the funeral establishment.
5 2. Disclosures. At the time an application is made, and prior to accepting the applicant's
6 initial premium or deposit for a pre-need insurance policy that is being sold in connection
7 with a prearranged funeral service or plan as described in Title 32, section 1402, a producer
8 shall adequately disclose the following information:
9 A. The fact that a pre-need insurance policy is involved or being used to fund a
10 prearranged funeral service or plan;
11 B. The nature of the relationship among the soliciting producer, the provider of the
12 funeral or cemetery merchandise or services, the administrator and any other person;
13 C. The relationship of the pre-need insurance policy to the funding of the prearranged
14 funeral service or plan and the nature and existence of any guarantees relating to the
15 prearranged funeral service or plan;
16 D. A list of the goods and services that are selected or contracted for in the prearranged
17 funeral service or plan and all relevant information concerning the price of the funeral
18 and burial services, including an indication that the purchase price is either guaranteed
19 at the time of purchase or to be determined at the time of need;
20 E. The fact that the face amount of the pre-need insurance policy may not exceed the
21 maximum amount of the goods and services that are contracted for in the prearranged
22 funeral service or plan;
23 F. All relevant information concerning what occurs and whether any entitlements or
24 obligations arise if there is a difference between the proceeds of the pre-need insurance
25 policy and the amount actually needed to fund the prearranged funeral service or plan;
26 G. Any penalties or restrictions, including, but not limited to, geographic restrictions
27 or the inability of the provider to perform, on the delivery of merchandise or services
28 or the prearranged funeral service or plan guarantee; and
29 H. Whether a sales commission or other form of compensation is being paid for the
30 sale of the pre-need insurance policy and the identity of the individual or entity to
31 whom it is paid.
32 Sec. 3. 32 MRSA §1401, sub-§1, as amended by PL 2007, c. 402, Pt. J, §1, is
33 further amended to read:
34 1. Plan requirements. Except as provided in subsection subsections 1‑A and 1-B,
35 any a prearranged funeral or burial plan contracted or undertaken within this State must
36 comply with the following.
37 A. All money paid during a person's lifetime to any individual, firm, association,
38 partnership or corporation, by that person or by someone on behalf of that person, under
39 an agreement that services will be performed or personal property will be delivered in
40 connection with the disposition of that person's body after death must be deposited by
41 the payee within 10 days after receipt of the money in a separate account in a financial
42 institution or credit union authorized to do business in this State, as defined in Title
43 9‑B, section 131, subsections 12‑A and 17‑A, in the name of the payee as mortuary
