1 Sec. 5. 32 MRSA §1401, sub-§1-B is enacted to read:
2 1-B. Plan funded with proceeds of pre-need life insurance policy. A prearranged
3 funeral service or plan may be funded with proceeds of a pre-need insurance policy in
4 accordance with this subsection. For the purposes of this section, "pre-need insurance" has
5 the same meaning as in Title 24-A, section 2176-A, subsection 1.
6 A. During a person's lifetime, a person or that person's legal representative may enter
7 into an agreement that services will be performed or personal property will be delivered
8 in connection with the disposition of that person's body after death by the assignment
9 of proceeds of a pre-need insurance policy to the funeral establishment upon that
10 person's death.
11 B. The face amount of a pre-need insurance policy sold in connection with a
12 prearranged funeral service or plan as described in section 1402 may not exceed the
13 maximum amount of the goods and services that are contracted for in the prearranged
14 funeral service or plan.
15 C. An agreement under paragraph A must be in writing and a copy must be furnished
16 to the person or the person's legal representative by the funeral establishment when the
17 agreement is executed. The agreement must identify the parties to the agreement and
18 must be signed by an authorized representative of the funeral establishment.
19 The receipt of a commission for the sale of pre-need insurance by a licensee that is also
20 licensed as an insurance producer does not constitute a violation of section 1455-B,
21 subsection 5.
22 This subsection may not be construed to alter the terms of an insurance policy or supersede
23 any law governing the regulation of insurance policies.
24 Sec. 6. 32 MRSA §1401, sub-§2, as enacted by PL 1999, c. 258, §2 and affected
25 by §3, is amended to read:
26 2. Rulemaking. The board shall adopt rules regarding prearranged funeral
27 agreements, including, but not limited to:
28 A. The form, format and content of trust agreements;
29 B. Standards regarding when service contracts are required in conjunction with trust
30 agreements and the form, format and content of the service contracts;
31 C. The establishment of reasonable fees that may be charged only pursuant to
32 subsection 1, paragraph D; and
33 D. Inspection of trust agreements, account information and any related
34 documentation.; and
35 E. The form, format and content of agreements for prearranged funeral services or
36 plans as described in section 1402 funded by pre-need insurance.
37 Rules adopted pursuant to this section are routine technical rules under the Maine Revised
38 Statutes, Title 5, chapter 375, subchapter II‑A 2-A.
