10 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
11 number to read consecutively.
12 SUMMARY
1133 This amendment replaces the bill and makes the following changes to the laws related
1144 to the sale of insurance in connection with prearranged funeral services or plans.
15 1. It eliminates a prohibition against funeral practitioners becoming licensed to sell
16 insurance.
17 2. It requires certain disclosures about pre-need insurance used to fund funeral
18 arrangements.
19 3. It requires that the face amount of a pre-need insurance policy may not exceed the
20 maximum amount of goods and services contracted for in a prearranged funeral service or
21 plan.
22 4. It authorizes the payment of commissions in connection with the sale of pre-need
23 insurance to fund funeral arrangements.
